(81, 1, '2015-07-17 01:03:52', '2015-07-17 01:03:52', '<p dir="ltr">Tony Cruse was born December 28, 1972 in Gainesville, Florida to Kenneth and Linda Cruse (Fisher). Tony grew up in High Springs, Florida, and in 1976 had a younger brother, Jason. Tony enjoyed playing baseball and hanging out with his friends. At an early age, he showed he was was very dedicated and showed great strength. One late Sunday evening, while he was riding his bike to church he fell, and had a compound fracture to his left arm. He was taken to the hospital, had his arm reset, and was back in school the next day. It was very important to him not to miss a day of school - not even for broken arm, showing his dedication to go on, even when it wasn''t easy.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">After graduating, he started working for at Carlon making electrical PVC pipe. During this time he began  volunteering as a Fire Fighter for City of High Springs, and soon realized he had a passion for serving others and his community. At the same time, he met Carolyn Sullivan who later became his wife. Together they had Mathew and Grace.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">After being laid off because of the down turn of construction at the time, he decided he wanted to follow his passion of serving his community. After obtaining a Law Enforcement Certification from Lake City Community College, he went on to became a Deputy Sheriff in Gilchrist . After a number years he worked his way to become Captain.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Tony also volunteered at the local Food Bank, and became a Mason of at Carlton Masonic Lodge. During this time he received numerous awards and citations for his service to his community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir="ltr">On March 23, 2013 he was told he had Pancreatic Cancer, and told he had 6 to 12 months left. On January 22, 2014 we lost Tony.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Kenneth Cruse, Retired Sargent for City of High Springs and Jason Cruse, Sargent for Alachua County Sheriff</p>', 'Memories', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-17 01:03:52', '2015-07-17 01:03:52', '', 18, 'http://www.pacfl.org/uncategorized/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
