(188, 1, '2015-09-20 16:45:34', '2015-09-20 16:45:34', '<span style="position: relative; font-size: 300%; font-family: Times New Roman; font-weight: bold;" class="first_letter">T</span><p dir="ltr">ony Cruse was born December 28, 1972 in Gainesville, Florida to Kenneth and Linda Cruse (Fisher). Tony grew up in High Springs and had a younger brother (Jason). Tony enjoyed playing baseball and hanging out with his friends. At an early age Tony showed he was very dedicated and showed great strength. On a late Sunday evening while Tony was riding his bike to church he fell off the bike and compound fractured his arm. Tony was taken to the hospital, had his arm reset, and was back in school the next morning. It was important to Tony to not miss a day a school for a broken arm. Tony showed this by never missing a day of school his entire school years.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">After Tony graduated, he started working for Carlon making electrical pipe. During this time, Tony became a Volunteer Fighter with the city of High Springs and realized he had a passion for serving others and his community.  Also, during this time of his life he met Carolyn Sullivan who would later become his wife. Tony and Carolyn had two children (Gracie and Matthew).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">After being laid off from Carlon, Tony decided he wanted to continue his passion of serving his community by becoming a Deputy Sheriff. Tony attended Lake City Community College and obtained his Law Enforcement Certification. Soon after Tony went to work for Gilchrist County Sheriff’s office in Trenton Florida and worked his way through the ranks and became Captain of this agency.  Tony also worked as Correctional Officer for Lancaster Correction Institution until he became sick. Tony furthered his service to the community by becoming heavily involved in the local food bank, being a member of the Carlton Masonic Lodge and a Shriner. During his time of serving his community, he received numerous awards.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Tony was always willing to help others and giving of himself to the community. Tony loved God, his family and his community.</p>', 'Memories', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-20 16:45:34', '2015-09-20 16:45:34', '', 18, 'http://www.pacfl.org/uncategorized/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
